page.title: 16SHEFFORD WILDLIFE
page.content: The Chicksands Priory was once beautiful parkland but now is a defence area and the public bridleway is closed. The rabbit population is recovering after being seriously affected by Myxomatosis.The fox is now only to be found in the wooded areas of Chicksands and Rowney Warren.The grey squirrel is very common in the wooded areas.Fallow Deer and Muntjak are fairly common, the Muntjak being decended from a small number which escaped from Woburn Park in the 1950's. Of the water birds, the Mallard is very common and Canada Geese have been nesting in the area since 1981.Swans, once common, are now rarely to be seen. There is little local land which is not either built on or farmed.
